# Hangman Game

A classic hangman game built with vanilla TypeScript, enabling players to guess hidden words by
typing letters. This project showcases the use of modern web technologies and provides a simple,
engaging user experience.

You can see a preview of the working application
[here](https://lisitsyna-anna.github.io/hangman-game/).

## Features

- Interactive Gameplay: Guess letters to reveal the hidden word.
- Score Tracking: Keeps track of your wins and losses.
- Responsive Design: Enjoy the game on any device.

## Technologies Used

The Hangman Game is built using the following technologies:

- HTML
- Tailwind
- TypeScript
- Vite
- GitHub Actions

## Installation

To run this application locally on your computer, you need to have TypeScript installed globally.

1. Clone this repository: `git clone https://github.com/lisitsyna-anna/hangman-game`
2. Change into the project directory: `cd hangman-game`
3. Install the dependencies: `npm install`
4. Start the development server: `npm run dev`
5. Open your browser and visit `http://http://localhost:5174/hangman-game` to view the application.

